OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 18 Jun to Sat 27 Jun
OL,6,FThe first few days of this period are
OL,7,Flikely to see something of a northwest-
OL,8,Fsoutheast split in the weather across
OL,9,Fthe UK. Areas towards the north and
OL,10,Fwest are most likely to often be
OL,11,Fcloudier, with spells of rain, some of
OL,12,Fwhich could be heavy and accompanied
OL,13,Fby breezy conditions. Further
OL,14,Fsoutheast, a greater chance of drier
OL,15,Fconditions, although given the
OL,16,Fpotential for high temperatures and
OL,17,Fhigh humidity, there is the
OL,18,Fpossibility of some thunderstorms
OL,19,Fbreaking out as well. Towards late
OL,20,FJune, there is a signal for more
OL,21,Fwidely settled conditions to develop
OL,22,Fwith high pressure more likely to
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fdominate, with temperatures probably
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fremaining above average for most.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1781385841
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 28 Jun to Sun 12 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is expected to lie close
OL,7,Fto the UK at the start of this period,
OL,8,Fbringing largely settled and dry
OL,9,Fconditions. Temperatures will likely
OL,10,Fbe above normal, with the potential
OL,11,Ffor hot conditions to develop,
OL,12,Fespecially in the south. Further into
OL,13,FJuly, the influence of high pressure
OL,14,Fmay weaken or shift more to the north
OL,15,For west of the UK, bringing an
OL,16,Fincreasing chance of more unsettled
OL,17,Fweather and thunderstorms, especially
OL,18,Fin the south. Temperatures will
OL,19,Fprobably ease back closer to normal
OL,20,Ftoo, although some warm and humid
OL,21,Fspells remain possible at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
